frameDefinitions: This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
An Entity (generally food) is exposed to a Heat_source whose Temperature may also be specified.
A Speaker addresses an Audience on a particular Topic.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
An Event begins at a certain Time and Place.
A Fuel, some flammable object or substance, ends up on fire.
frameExamples: Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
Bacon was <t>frying</t> in the pan, and a great heap of eggs already lay steaming on a plate.
McNamara <t>addressed</t> congress on the state of affairs of the Department of Defense.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Kindler</fen> is the person performing the intentional act.
The <fen>Flame</fen> is what is created by the Kindler.
The Flamables is the the object that is set on fire by the Kindler.
The cause of the fire.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event takes place.
The <fen>Entity</fen> (often a food item)  that absorbs heat.
The <fen>Container</fen> that holds the <fen>Entity</fen> that absorbs the heat.
This role identifies the object that directly supplies heat to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the heat absorption takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application occurs.
The person or persons to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> delivers their text.
The person who orally delivers a text about a <fen>Topic</fen> to a passive <fen>Audience</fen>.
What the text that the <fen>Speaker</fen> produces is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> describes when the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the speaking occurs.
The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
Name of the <fen>Event</fen> which occurs.
When the <fen>Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Event</fen> takes place.

The total material currently involved in combustion, including both the parts of the <fen>Fuel</fen> currently undergoing chemical alteration and the partially ionized gas that results from this process.
The entity that is begins to undergo rapid chemical alteration leading to damage or destruction.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fire</fen> begins to burn.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Fire</fen> begins to burn.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Mark</fex> started the fire with a magnifying glass.
<fex>Bacon</fex> frying in the pan and scenting the air
Five fat sausages were frying <fex>in the pan</fex>
Food was placed to sizzle <fex>on the barbecue </fex>.
<fex>Five minutes ago</fex>the eggs weren't boiling yet.
<fex>In the kitchen</fex> the meat sizzled in the oven and a big pan of potatoes stood on the hob
He lectured <fex>to the officers of the Scots Guard</fex>  in  1929.
<fex>You</fex> have to sermonize about the good times
He was the Director: he could lecture <fex>on whomever he liked</fex>.
Hot coals glowed <fex>behind the fire grate</fex>.
<fex>In the morning</fex> the grass glistened with dew
<fex>Outside</fex> something was shimmering on the shore.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: the National Tsunami Hazard Mitigation Program
